==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tresayle
<hw>Tres"ayle`</hw> <pr>(tr⟦ecr⟧s"⟦amac⟧l`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>trisa⟦ium⟧eul</ets>, from L. <ets>tris</ets>, <ets>tres</ets>,
three + F. <ets>a⟦ium⟧eul</ets> grandfather. Cf. <er>Besaiel</er>, and
see <er>Ayle</er>.]</ety> <def>A grandfather's grandfather.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Writ of tresayle</b></col> <fld>(O. Eng. Law)</fld>,
<cd>a writ which lay for a man claiming as heir to his grandfather's
grandfather, to recover lands of which he had been deprived by an
abatement happening on the ancestor's death.</cd> <rj><au>Mozley &
W.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tresor</ent>⟦br⟧
